This repository contains class-trimmed derivatives of:

  - Ultralytics YOLO26 (yolo26m, yolo26l, yolo26x)
    Source: https://huggingface.co/Ultralytics/YOLO26
    Upstream: https://github.com/ultralytics/ultralytics
    License: AGPL-3.0

  - Ultralytics YOLOv11 (yolov11l)
    Source: Ultralytics' default model registry
    Upstream: https://github.com/ultralytics/ultralytics
    License: AGPL-3.0

The trimmed weights in each variant directory are produced by slicing
the classification head's output Conv2d layers along the
output-channel axis, keeping only the rows corresponding to the 15
class IDs documented in `trim.json`. No further training is performed;
all retained-class weights are byte-identical to upstream.

Because these artefacts are derivatives of AGPL-3.0 weights, any
network-deployed service that uses them must also comply with AGPL-3.0
(make corresponding source available to users interacting with the
service over a network).

Trimming script: tools/train-detector/trim-classes.py in the fnvr
project (https://github.com/fnvr-project — adjust to actual repo URL).
Export shape:
  - GPU variants → DeepStream-Yolo's export_yolo26.py
  - Hailo variant → vanilla Ultralytics ONNX (opset 11, NMS stripped)
